text: Gregory Robert Jennett (born 15 August 1968) is an Australian television presenter and journalist. ==Biography== Jennett completed his high school education at Newington College in 1986.Newington College Register of Past Students 1863–1998 (Syd, 1999) pp100 He has been a journalist since 1995 and reports politics for the Australian Broadcasting Corporation. He started in radio and then moved to television news. Jennett is currently the presenter of the Capital Hill program on ABC News 24.About ABC News Retrieved 27 May 2015. ==References== Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:People educated at Newington College Category:ABC News (Australia) presenters Category:Australian television journalists Category:ABC radio (Australia) journalists and presenters
